B2:

Prerequisites (already installed on your system)

· Jenkins running (http://localhost:8080)
· Docker installed on the Jenkins agent (your Windows machine)
· Git installed
· Jenkins plugins: Pipeline, Git, Credentials Binding, Docker Pipeline

---

Step 1: Prepare your Git repository

Create a repository (local or GitHub) with these three files:

HelloWorld.java

```java
public class HelloWorld {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello from Jenkins!");
    }
}
```

Dockerfile

```dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY HelloWorld.java .
RUN javac HelloWorld.java
CMD ["java", "HelloWorld"]
```

Jenkinsfile (the pipeline definition)

```groovy
pipeline {
    agent any
    environment {
        DOCKER_CREDENTIAL_ID = 'Docker'   // matches your Jenkins credential ID
        IMAGE_NAME = ''   // your Docker Hub repo
    }
    stages {
        stage('Build Java Application') {
            steps {
                bat 'javac HelloWorld.java'
            }
        }
        stage('Run Java Program') {
            steps {
                bat 'java HelloWorld'
            }
        }
        stage('Build Docker Image') {
            steps {
                bat "docker build -t ${env.IMAGE_NAME}:latest ."
            }
        }
        stage('Login to DockerHub') {
            steps {
                withCredentials([usernamePassword(
                    credentialsId: env.DOCKER_CREDENTIAL_ID,
                    usernameVariable: 'USER',
                    passwordVariable: 'PASS'
                )]) {
                    bat "docker login -u %USER% -p %PASS%"
                }
            }
        }
        stage('Push Docker Image') {
            steps {
                bat "docker push ${env.IMAGE_NAME}:latest"
            }
        }
    }
    post {
        always {
            bat 'docker logout'
        }
    }
}
```

